title: For Sale:  Allin conversion Springfield trap door
postcontent: I have a solid example of a Springfield rifled musket that has an Alin trapdoor conversion. Comes with some 50.70 ammo (about 30 rounds). I will entertain trades of comparable value with interest in SIG hand guns, A/R's or etc.  Make an offer! This trap door is fun to shoot and has little kick.This is a very unique piece of history nearly impossible to find. Built as a rifled musket in 1864 during the American Civil War and modified by Alin into a prototype trap door for the government in 1866 (retaining the .50/70 caliber). These were the predecessor to the popular .45/70 trap doors of the late 19th century.There were few of these made and fewer surviving.If it is listed it is available!While not similar in condition, here's the story on the rifle: http://www.nramuseum.org/guns/the-galleries/the-american-west-1850-to-1900/case-18-hunting-and-military-arms-on-the-western-frontier/us-springfield-allin-conversion-model-1866.aspxTrades will be considered with adjusting $ for equality of value.
